In[29]:
cols = ["n_reads", "per_mapped", "per_cov5", "pcr_pf_parasitaemia"]
n_cols = len(cols)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, n_cols, figsize=(n_cols*3, 6))

fig.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.075)

for col, ax in zip(cols, ax.flatten()):
    sns.stripplot(y="province",
                  x=col,
                  alpha=0.6,
                  data=df, 
                  hue="province",
                  palette="tab20",
                  legend=False,
                  ax=ax)
    sns.boxplot(y="province",
                x=col,
                color='white',
                data=df,
                showfliers=False,
                ax=ax)
    
    ax.set_xlabel(col)
    ax.set_ylabel("")
    ax.label_outer()
    
    if col == "pcr_pf_parasitaemia":
        ax.set_xscale("log")
In[19]:
provinces = df["province"].unique()
prov_cols = dict(zip(provinces, sns.color_palette("tab20", len(provinces))))
In[20]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(6, 6))

for prov, gdf in df.groupby("province"):
    ax.scatter(x="n_reads",
               y="per_mapped",
               alpha=0.8,
               s=15,
               color=prov_cols[prov],
               label=prov,
               data=gdf)
    
# Labels
ax.set_xlabel("No. Reads")
ax.set_ylabel("Mapping Percentage")

# Legend
ax.legend()
